<subSubSection lastPageId="82" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="81.[151,1437,1764,2043]" lastBlockId="82.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="82" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1836,1862]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Remarks</emphasis>
. The placement of this species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lilljeborg" authorityYear="1865" box="[680,740,1837,1862]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[680,740,1837,1862]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Tiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been reviewed, mostly because of the few and rather poor illustrations. Since its description (
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, A. O." box="[597,740,1872,1898]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="229 - 300" refId="ref50631" refString="Walker, A. O. (1904) Report on the Amphipoda collected by Professor Herdman, at Ceylon, in 1902. Ceylon Pearl Oyster Fisheries, Supplementary Reports, 17, 229 - 300." type="journal article" year="1904">Walker 1904</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1904" box="[755,938,1872,1898]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[755,938,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Tiron thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has appeared in the literature mainly in keys to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lilljeborg" authorityYear="1865" box="[182,242,1909,1934]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,242,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Tiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, separated out on account of an unusual outer plate of the maxilliped. The present review of the tironins makes it possible to compare this species with others in the currently recognised genera.According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, A. O." box="[1276,1436,1944,1970]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" pagination="229 - 300" refId="ref50631" refString="Walker, A. O. (1904) Report on the Amphipoda collected by Professor Herdman, at Ceylon, in 1902. Ceylon Pearl Oyster Fisheries, Supplementary Reports, 17, 229 - 300." type="journal article" year="1904">Walker (1904)</bibRefCitation>
the species has a short, moderately curved and distally widening gnathopod 1 basis similar to species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[1323,1429,1981,2006]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1323,1429,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">Minitiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, contrasting with the elongate, straight gnathopod 1 basis of equal width throughout found in all other tironins. Fur- thermore the species has stubby pereopods 3–7 (although poorly illustrated), and unusual, concave maxillipedal outer plates closely similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Hirayama" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[499,709,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galeatus">
<emphasis box="[499,709,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Minitiron galeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[782,849,187,213]" name="Japan" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Although many details remain to be learned about Walker’s 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1904" box="[259,444,223,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[259,444,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Tiron thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, notably the 
<typeStatus box="[594,642,223,249]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
of setal spines on the outer plate spine-row and shape and size of the inner plate of maxilla 1, the species is here tentatively transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[919,1025,259,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[919,1025,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Minitiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
